What you need to know:

As a young girl, Nadia Abdalla always  had her eyes set on the position of the Secretary General (SG) of the United Nations.To her, joining the public service as CAS at just 28 years to sit at a decision-making level, is a testament of her conviction early in life.Before joining the civil service, Ms Abdalla was an aggressive young woman leveraging on social media to make a living.